FBIS4-16173 "drsov072_a_94017" FBIS-SOV-94-072 Daily Report 14 Apr 1994 RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS Air Defense Troops Force Down U.S. Plane Air Defense Troops Force Down U.S. Plane LD1404091294 Moscow Ostankino Television First Channel Network in Russian 0800 GMT 14 Apr 94 LD1404091294 Moscow Ostankino Television First Channel Network Russian BFN [From the "Novosti" newscast] [Excerpts] Russian air defense aircraft have intercepted a small U.S. private airplane over Kamchatka and forced it to land on our territory because it had violated Russian airspace. After the circumstances were clarified, the airplane was refuelled and allowed to continue its flight. [passage omitted] INTERFAX reports that Russian air defense troops were alerted by the fact that when the private jet violated flight rules an American RSI-135 [as heard] spy aircraft was flying near the Russian state border at the same altitude and at the same speed. An investigation into the incident has started.
